content:
Beautiful game and very long, there's lot of to do and play. The maingame 
is long and then there is also quite long bonusgame. Story is good and the 
bonusgame story fits in the maingames storyline. There is different kinds 
of minigames, not just hidden objects. Map works very well and that's 
important because you need to go back and forward between different places. 
Couple of times game did freeze and I have to restart but not too bad, not 
like the first of this serie (that was just terrible). Overall good game.

content: Very good games as ever

So far beautiful imagery and nice music/sounds. Hilariously bad voice acting. The cut scenes are kind of laggy, but no crashes yet.The main character is kind of meh, but I like the setting. I'm very thankful for the map teleportation and hints because it's easy to get lost. I don't think the morphing objects make sense. They tend to look like normal items in the setting, nothing standing out, certainly not magical. Edit: one of the puzzles I completed would not register, so I had to skip to move forward.
Love this game, it's long but not boring well worth the money.
Great story and graphics. I always love these games!

1st time trying this game company on these type of games. Absolutely love the game! Get your money's worth compared to other companies. Fantastic artwork, gameplay, storyline & you give a map where you can jump from place to place and hint or choose gameplay guide to help if you get stuck. Most importantly, on top of this, you give value for value on the length of the game. Great job! You got me on 1 of your sales and you got me hooked on this series.

Good puzzles. The game is fairly lengthy but I have to wonder if it just seems that way because the sceen transitions are sooooo slooooow. Got to the point where even the animations of chopping wood etc were frustrating as I felt I spent way too much time just waiting for something to complete. Also towards the end there is a huge amount of back and forth just to collect or place a single item. So combined with the slow transition from one location to the next, it detracts from overall gameplay due to increasing levels of frustration. Without such frustrations it'd probably be a much shorter game.

Perhaps the best of the three Lost Lands games I've played so far and worth a five star rating! Sadly, the four horsemen premise is almost entirely hoky and has very little connection to the four horsemen of the Revelation of Saint John (see chapter six.) Nice try though... Two problems common to most Five-BN games persist. These are:- a. mini-games are almost always too hard and b. collecting hard to spot items on story screens is an exercise in frustration. But this is a very long game! Think 10+ hours. Yay...

Okay game but could have been a great game. Great graphics and sound. The story is cliche but manageable. Too much fetching of illogical items from very far maps. I had to hit the hint button a lot because although I knew how to solve the puzzle, I could not remember which map it resided in. The troll wanting to talk through every item description was annoying.  There was a puzzle partially hidden behind the item/possession possession tray so only it could only be solved by trying all possible combinations. Finally, the main character did not fit the story, and she never looked in place at any scene!

Another great game by these guys. Interesting, lots of puzzles, fluid, map was great, the only thing that got slightly annoying was the dwarf telling you what everything was. I didn't mind it the first time but then every time you touched it even by accident he'd start talking again, it's not massively off putting. I liked how the bonus game linked itself to the main game. Definitely worth playing if you like these types of games. I've already played all FIVE-BN games and can't wait to see what's next.

This game was 85% tedious fetching of cliched items, 10% "find the silhoutted items in the UNcluttered room", 3% super easy "arrange the items correctly" minigames, and 2% story full of stolen bits from Harry Potter and LOTR.  I became so tired of finding an item, which allowed me to find the next one, and so on, ad nauseam, that only my OCD drove me to complete it.  And the way that loud troll guy's dialogue kept cueing up over and over everytime I tapped the screen!  The nice graphics ain't worth it.

I have played a lot of HOG and I have to say this is right up there for one of the best I have ever seen. To begin with, the story was 8/10 and I am hard to please. The art work, 7/10, not as much detail as I prefer but still lovely. Tons of areas to explore! The background noise is just right for the moods. The cut scenes are very well done. I am not too impressed by the characters talking tho, very stiff. The puzzles are fun without being impossible and the HO scenes are only so so. This game keeps you moving all around the whole world right up till the end, thank goodness for the map. The bonus chapter is nice too, not very long but they never are. Replayability? 7/10
